The paper discusses attribute-based encryption and its potential applications in cloud and distributed computing environments. This topic falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the implementation of a distributed storage system, which falls under the category of databases (cs.DB) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper discusses the potential for future work in the area of attribute-based encryption, which could fall under the category of cryptography (cs.CY).
